have you even wondered why does the pyro play the air guitar on his axe why does the medic pretend that his saw is a violin whats up with the corny texan guitar why the hell is there a dance dance immolation achievement thats because you are not in on the ruse tf2 is not a shooter game its a rhythm game you can have excellent reflex and aim and still get outplayed by a player with a better timing who through his understanding of the game mechanics and his immediate environment will force you to play to his tune someone who will forestall your attack and press on intuitively and instinctively without leaving you any room for action other than a panicked defense this may sound familiar to a seasoned gamer and should not be surprising in xvii century miyamoto musashi writes in the book of five rings there is timing in everything timing in strategy cannot be mastered without a great deal of practice [] timing and rhythm are involved in the military arts shooting bows and guns and riding horses [] there is timing in the whole life of the warrior in his thriving and declining in his harmony and discord the book of five rings describes ni ten ichi ryu or the way of strategy as applied to sword fighting the focus of this school is a straightforward thoroughly utilitarian style relying on timing strength and throwing the opponent offbalance lets take a look how some of its techniques apply to tf2 attitude noattitude whenever you parry hit spring strike or touch the enemys cutting sword you must cut the enemy in the same movement it is essential to attain this if you think only of hitting springing striking or touching the enemy you will not be able actually to cut him more than anything you must be thinking of carrying your movement through to cutting him as applied to tf2 you should instinctively choose the right weapon to counter the enemy and make every ammo count the difference between one well and one poorly placed shotgun shot is half of your life make sure it counts ken no sen advance with as strong a spirit as possible and when you reach the enemy move with your feet a little quicker than normal unsettling him and overwhelming him sharply  a good example is a pyro attacking with the powerjack or soldier with the concheror inexperienced players will panic when faced with such a threat tai no sen when the enemy attacks remain undisturbed but feign weakness as the enemy reaches you suddenly move away indicating that you intend to jump aside then dash in attacking strongly as soon as you see the enemy relax convenient in confined spaces feign retreat for a medkit turn around the corner and renew your attack also relevant for triplejumping scouts and stairstabbing spies tai tai no sen when the enemy makes a quick attack you must attack strongly and calmly aim for his weak point as he draws near and strongly defeat him or if the enemy attacks calmly you must observe his movements and with your body rather floating join in with his movements as he draws near move quickly and cut him strongly  important for amby spies and huntsman snipers dont panic maintain your distance and aim for the head or go for a sidestabbushwacka crit while timing your movement appropriately to hit the enemy in one timing when you have closed with the enemy to hit him as quickly and directly as possible while you see that he is still undecided the timing of hitting before the enemy decides to withdraw break or hit is this in one timing note that this is not ambushing this is about taking initiative automatically without overthinking when your enemy has not yet responded the body in place of the long sword according to the enemys cutting method you can dash against him with your body first and afterwards cut with the sword do not use the melee only as the last resort if your opponent is momentarily disoriented close in and attack with the melee to confuse him then take a step back and finish off with a secondary using melee when possible also saves you reload time do not use against suicidal classes with explosive projectiles depending on the place chase [the enemy] towards awkward places and try to keep him with his back to awkward places when the enemy gets into an inconvenient position do not let him look around but conscientiously chase him around and pin him down always chase the enemy into bad footholds obstacles at the side and so on using the virtues of the place to establish predominant positions from which to fight the use of environment is not just pushing the enemy off cliffs force the opponent into rocks cactuses and other obstacles that will break the flow of his movement and give you the advantage to know the times to know the enemys disposition in battle is it flourishing or waning when in a duel you must forestall the enemy and attack when you have first recognized his school of strategy perceived his quality and his strong and weak points attack in an unsuspecting manner knowing his metre and modulation and the appropriate timing if you are thorougly conversant with strategy you will recognise the enemys intentions and thus have many opportunities to win  a crucial element of each duel give it some thought to hold down a shadow in single combat hold down the enemys strong intention with a suitable timing and defeat him by forestalling him with this timing particularly important when playing pyro use the airblast to counter the enemy advance and position yourself for a kill to crush in single combat if the enemy is less skillful than ourselves if his rhythm is disorganized or if he has fallen into evasive or retreating attitudes we must crush him straightaway with no concern for his presence and without allowing him space for breath it is essential to crush him all at once the primary thing is not to let him recover his position even a little dont let a weakened enemy retreat consider that you have a much better chance killing him when he is weakened and retreating than after he returns healed do not let deadringer spies escape to throw in confusion observing the enemys spirit we can make him think here there like that like this slow fast victory is certain when the enemy is caught up in a rhythm which confuses his spirit in single combat we can confuse the enemy by attacking with varied techniques when the chance arises feint a thrust or cut or make the enemy think you are going to close with him and when he is confused you can easily win once again force the enemy to play to your tune and abandon his usual approach airblasting or dodging projectiles changing distance and switching to melee when appropriate is a good example tldr those techniques share certain common themes to become a better player simply follow the rules of the way of strategy 1 do not think dishonestly you wont become better if you dont face your enemy directly 2 the way is in training practice your timing counters and approaches 3 become acquainted with every art know all your weapons and map geometry 4 know the ways of all professions know all the classes 5 distinguish between gain and loss in worldly matters know when to retreat and which enemies to prioritize dont die blindly following one enemy 6 develop intuitive judgment and understanding for everything 7 perceive those things which cannot be seen intuit into others intents spycheck 8 pay attention even to trifles listen carefully to the sounds pay attention to your peripheral vision including kill feed 9 do nothing which is of no use make sure your actions are purposeful
