alright its been a long time since i decided to have a legitamite review of tf2 up but i feel like its time to bring one back as a person whos sunk over 4000 hours into this game youre gonna bet this is gonna be a positive review my old review was pretty damn cruddy in the first place so i made it into a joke afterwards because it was the corniest pile of screws ive ever very poorly composed my first point to make the variety 9 classes was enough for a ton of people to buy this game even without hats new weapons or too many mapsgamemodes if thats not enough each gamemode has been updated to have atleast 3 maps except for tc tc only has one map and thats tc_hydro the objective of tc is to advance a couple stages capture the enemys point and protect yours in other words attack and defend cp maps minus the rest of the map as mentioned earlier a large amount of new content has spread around the game with the sniper vs spy update there came hats only a few but still hats i wasnt there myself but i can bet it wouldve been my new favorite toy the weapons which have been made at least once a year are always a nice twist to the game adding a new form of strategy offense defense andor mobility all weapons are a spice to that one bowl of noodles that make it seem like an entirely different game my second point to be mentioned how it was made tf2 has an odd way of how it was first born and how it eventually came to be what we love today starting as a simple quake mod made by 3 people its hard to believe that it became the tf2 that we or i love and know today it grew pretty damn quickly had its own maps in quake and was a huge hit in quake and team fortress quake was probably the biggest leap in what lead to tf2s hype well not tf2s hype valve eventually decided to accept them into them at their large success and allowed the production of a game on the halflife engine that was team fortress classic it was a higher balanced smoothed better quality game of team fortress theres not much else to say about it its last update was 2004 the community had not completely given up on staying with tfcs system a new game called fortress forever theres not much to say about it it was a slightly better version of tfc it never really did make it too far considering tf2 came out only one month later since then it has recieved multiple updates changes andor tweaks on tf2 my third point that is well the most interesting part of tf2 in my opinion the lore yep the lore its not well known to most tf2 players and most hardly ever take note of it alongside the updates every once in awhile tf2 always hides a little something that the community likes to take up on itself the love and war update for example it had an ongoing line of hints that there would be an update revolving bread and currently people believe there is a engi vs spy update coming up based on game file updates theres also comics that tf2 releases once in awhile the mention of jarate had a comic itself im not going to go into much detail about the lore because most of the fun of it is figuring the small things out yourself the fourth part i myself find a major detail that tf2 really adds trading yeah trading its gone downhill recently and many are quitting because of this im not going to go much detail about this cause its not really necessary in tf2 that you need hats but being able to trade weapons and cosmetics is a large part of tf2 being able to stem out in many directions tf2s economy has grasped an interesting way to donate to the game creators especially valve just know that when you buy something off of the mann co store the person who made that is payed and youre increasing the development speed of hl3 the fifth part of this review is simply put community now i cant stay positive with this entirely tf2s community is well odd to define tf2 is so far out there that it grabs attention of a lot of people its jammed with weebs and bronies not saying either of those are bad things to everyone i myself find both of those annoying at times as most most of them stay sitting in their own servers theres communitymade maps communitymade hats communitymade guns not saying that valves always too happy to accept those that or its just trying to form a suicide pact there are a lot of people in tf2 and its hard to pinpoint what would define tf2s community other than an evergrowing vast black hole and it sure as hell isnt going down just because the trading is going down the sixth and final part of this review extra stuff if you dont like fighting in tf2 and arent too happy with trading then thats alright theres tons of community created stuff that valve doesnt accept into the game that can still be ported into the game as a custom map custom weapon custom gamemode or something of the sort this cant really be put into a positive or negative form as im happy with how some of this turns out and some of it is well cannon fodder because the extra bits and pieces of tf2 are such a large piece of what makes tf2 so addicting ill be putting this into well just what its meant to be extra bits and pieces the weapons these can be found pretty much anywhere whether its on a times ten server tf2 tightrope hale or weaponizer most of these ideas are original or simple modifications of a weapon most of these add a spice to it that fulfill a gamemode or class to maximize what it was made for and accept it as an additional piece of the game when i say weapons most of what has been claimed is well a gamemode weapon yes most of its a gamemode weapon and you have to play the gamemode to actually experience it while it is rather strict the tf2 community is always coming up with new stats new models and new ways to play the game with weapons via the workshop the hats and cosmetics this is probably going to be my shortest paragraph to exist on this review its via the workshop valve gives you examples on what to make it with you make it it gets accepted you get some greens not paid mods but well content that becomes official the gamemodes whether its forming tf2 into a horror game with a dark enviroment somewhat scary unkillable bosses that crisp you alive or dragging yourself against a slope at lightspeed with flashy lights and upbeat music the gamemodes can easily turn what you thought was tf2 into something out of its capacity now when i say gamemodes i dont mean noncompetitive gamemodes those are gonna be in here for damn sure alongside weapons being added to fully experience a gamemode theres also competitive gamemodes ultiduo mge 6s 4s and highlander these gamemodes are also accomodated with websites with competitive tf2 involved including ugc etf2l asiafortress and much more theres badges lan tournaments and bets placed on players that can easily turn tf2 into a fun nonprofit game into a competitive sweaty tryhard moshpit where you want to win with everything you got not saying that it really is that competitive most tf2 competitive players are making jokes and get along pretty damn well in the community but it does go large when the players make it so i guess thats my review on tf2 8 years after its release still a large growing community with updates that supplies and endless amount of content that well does what its made for scare you infuriate you or make you feel like you could dig your fingers into a tree because you play it so ed much tf2s one hell of a game that i couldnt imagine ever dying out
