to put it shortly team fortress 2 is a competitive multiplayer fps with a loose spytech aesthetic and is one of valves more popular monetary juggernauts it was originally released in 2007 and was included in the orange box players choose from one of 2 teams and one of 9 classes and must fight to complete objectives for their chosen team that vary by game mode they can choose from a variety of weapons to aid in their missions and wear cool hats while doing so if they so choose valve are still generously and freely updating the game even more than half a decade after it was released with new bugfixes maps game modes and weapons they should however take a break  more on this below objectives range from capturing andor defending control points to capturing enemy intelligence while defending yours to pushing large bombs along rails to destroy the enemy base to banding together and fighting waves of killer robots and more there is a lot of variety here to say nothing of the custom maps and unofficial modes some of these are more prevalent than others however  not every mode fits the game equally well players are able to randomly find craft purchase from the microtransaction store or trade for different weapons that they can equip tf2 is not strictly paytowin because you are not required to spend money to gain weapons although it may be the fastest way to get them its also worth knowing that the default weapons are generally good and most of the other weapons are sidegrades most of them not all  a handful are still direct upgrades for some reason new players start off with only 50 inventory slots for any weapons they find if a player wants more space  and they probably will considering how many weapons there are these days  theyll have to go premium with a onetime microtransaction purchase there is also a much larger amount of optional cosmetic items to put on your characters acquired in largely the same way as the weapons these are completely optional but given that most tf2 players want to look pretty there is a sizable ingame trading economy that largely focuses on these cosmetic items of note are the keys used to open mann co crates which largely resemble a form of slot machine  except modern crates usually give you something nice killstreak counters that grant graphical effects weapons with persistent kill counters different taunts and of course more hats this is also completely optional and frankly an auxillary game function that i wish people wouldnt pay so much attention to keys also serve as one of the currencies in the tf2conomy and thats how valve makes money from this game dont be put off by the hats  team fortress 2 has some good gameplay the 9 classes are grouped into three categories which are more like loose guidelines and should be regarded as such the attack classes are the fast and doublejumping scout the jackofalltrades rocketslinging soldier and the flamethrowing ambushing pyro the defense classes are the versatile bombchucking demoman the heavy weapons guy with the huge miniguns and the engineer with his helpful buildings the support classes are the reallyquiteimportant medic the sniper and the backstabbing disguising cloaking sabotaging trickster spy most of the classes deliver differing gameplay experiences due to their abilities and mechanics this means that you can play just one or two classes that you really like or switch between any of the classes that your team or situation may need this is because the classes largely serve to fill separate niches and an effective team will contain a variety of classes  with some being more generally useful than others given the nature of the game youre bound to occasionally come across majority spy andor sniper teams which can be funny or annoying depending on your perspective tf2s general gameplay is slower than its halflife mod forebear team fortress classic and the original tf mod for quake especially when you compare player movement speeds this is however balanced by the more tactical nature of gameplay overall tactics revolve around frontlines and offensivedefensive pushes with the medics bercharges playing a vital role longtime veterans have also developed explosivejumping strategies for the soldier and demoman that can rival the player mobility of tfc as they fly towards the front lines this is of course assuming that you find a server with skilled enough players lowerlevel public servers including most of the official servers dont usually have the camraderie unfortunately there dont seem to be as many around as there was back when new weapons were regularly coming out around 20112013 but that could just be me tf2 doesnt take itself too seriously so you should be prepared to come across relatively easygoing players and matches as well if you find yourself dissatisfied or complaining about a game like this competitive tf2 is only growing stronger and pickup games or lobbies are good places to play more seriously  or even enter the scene proper with all this in mind you could compare tf2 to a sort of mmo fps it had persistent items and gameplay experiences that are built the same but can play out differently due to differing player tactics try playing the same 5 control point map for a while and youll see what i mean one other thing to note is that valve treats this game as a testbed an area for testing ideas that might not work so well the first time around this is just a useful thing to keep in mind i also mentioned that valve has continually added content to the game for most of its existence  from 2008 onward  which is especially admirable since theyve taken to adding communitycreated content unfortunately most of what theyve been adding for a while now has been large amounts of communitycreated cosmetic items since theres several hundreds of them in the game now along with oodles of particle effects weapons and other thingsthe size of the game has ballooned and optimization has taken a nosedive i really hope they take time off from their stated content first policy to do some housecleaning until then youll want a decently powerful machine to play this on  but avoid nvidia cards they dont like this games distinctive phong shading effect valves balancing act is not perfect either they continually make changes & additions that are not always wise and that some of the playerbase love to argue about overall though the game is usually balanced enough to have fun with while i recommend team fortress 2 as a great game overall i must also recommend you avoid the old steam users forums board for the game its an insular morose community of whiners who spam dumb memes and tired arguments and the remaining moderators seem to have all but gone into hiding if nothing else about tf2 interests you please at least take my advice on spuf
