team fortress 2 review game grade a explanation for rating team fortress 2 or tf2 is a wonderfully comical first person shooter the game does not focus on graphics or realism by any means unless beating down your foes with a lollypop is normal for you tf2 is quite enjoyable from a comical standpoint which is outstandingly hilarious something else you can enjoy in the game is the balanced game play will be addressed later in the review the replay value of tf2 is rather high due to the countless modded servers and new equipment you can unlock the game is very fun and you can rest knowing that the download time was well worth it seeing its a free game the only thing spent is time team fortress has a very unique and comical first person shooter aspect to it the fighting in the game is all based off of comedy weapons can range from a smelly fish to an actual hand cannon like weapons the equipment is quite entertaining for all of you that like first person shooters you shouldnt be afraid of this loss in realism there are still satisfying damage accuracy and unlocking systems that are involved this will keep you coming back to the game for newer and better weapons andor equipment in all combat is fun and takes skill to master the battlefield i think everyone can agree many games with potential are ruined by a paytowin system this is not true for tf2 every weapon and piece of equipment can be unlocked randomly throughout the game you can however pay to get something quicker also you are given crates which can be unlocked with a purchased key but again all the stuff can be earned some things are harder to get than others so dont expect to get all the great equipment right off the bat to sum it all up combat is fair and balanced as in most games people create modded servers these modded servers are for the most part fair and do not kill the game these servers tend to have the most people because they are very enjoyable while we are on the topic of players i would like to address the player base unfortunately there are some immature people on the mic you can avoid this problem by muting them and falling back into the focus of the game play other than that the community is still active and rather fun to play with all in all team fortress 2 is worth a try it is a great game you can play with friends and work forever on getting all the achievements if you are active in the steam market items can be traded and sold with ease i can promise you that you wont regret downloading this game
