reviews for the deaf and hard of hearing rereviewing  overall game tf2 is fantastic there are a horde of game modes to play that can keep you coming back to this old game for a while while i prefer mvm these days i do often play community servers for a good ctf or payload round accessibility gameplay like most fps games tf2 uses wasd space and control for mobilityrelated issues keys can be easily rebound to whatever suit your capabilities i rebound cruch to space and jump to a side mouse key for example as for sound with the exception of spies and spyrelated events such as sapping of your equipment there are visual cues to accompany the audio for some weapons that you can hear being fired you may not be able to see that youre being shot at such as some sniper rifles this is something to watch out for for gameplay accessibility i give it 1010 you can realistically play and succeed at all of the normal nonmod game modes available with or without sound subtitles & captions for deafhoh gamers tf2 offers subtitles and captions  something valve has a solid history of providing ive found the default captions lacking in mvm however fortunately there is a way to use external captions and i have turned to clovervidia for that httpsteamcommunitycomsharedfilesfiledetailsid167785751 as a deaf gamer i use captions over subtitles whenever i have the choice as the distinction tends to be between important information in captions and flavor text in subtitles that said i have not used the subtitles option for tf2 for captions i give it 610 normally 910 with external captions such as from clovervidia chattingcommunicating tf2 supports ingame voice communication but the pacing of the game does not make it essential gameplay can tolerate typing so many other players in servers tend to have no problem accommodating having to type even so many game modes dont require much communication for casual play for mvm typing can be made difficult at times and this problem can be exacerbated by queuing random teams each time you play and having to explain things repeatedly which can be a gamble ive written a guide to try to standardize voicebind calls in mvm until valve changes voicebinds to be more inclusive if ever httpsteamcommunitycomsharedfilesfiledetailsid358478951 overall accessibility tf2 incorporates visual signals for almost everything that happens in game its ability to rebind keys and add custom captions make it pretty accessible for most deficits in the gaming population overall 910
