tf2 at its core is an amazing game and one of the most fun and balanced shooters ive ever played even though choices by valve have tarnished its reputation and i mean they really screwed the pooch on more than one occasion it still stands out as one of the most fun and addicting shooters there is however to get the full enjoyment out of it you either need to find a community server which since quickplay started defaulting only to valve servers is becoming harder or play competitive valves public servers have little to no team cohesion or coordination owing to the freetoplay system bringing in lots of children dont worry if you get destroyed by more experienced players youll get better trial by fire worked for me if you need help ask you cant be an asset to your team if you have no clue what youre doing ask for tips from experienced players and always remember that there is a wiki [wikiteamfortresscom]  and for gods sake use a ing mic dont have a mic get one teamwork and communication is key the game isnt what it used to be you cant drop in to a random server and expect to find competent and friendly players anymore the visually appealing and unique artstyle has been destroyed by cashgrab cosmetics and the actual performance of the game has been destroyed by the added weight of the cosmetics still even as frustrating as it can be theres never anything more satisfying than coordinating a team through a difficult push to win a close victory also a final note if the server you join has an motd read it
