ah team fortress 2 lets get down to the basics tf2 is a classbased first person shooter made by a very successful company named valve valve is the creators behind famous titles such as left 4 dead counter strike and halflife tf2 started as a mod for quake and slowly evolved over a 7 year editing period tf2 was finally created and it was a hit to put this in retrospective here is an example team fortress 2 launched in 2007 and now its 2014 this game just simply wont die tf2 has 9 classes that are unique in their own way each class having its weaknesses and strong points making every class equal and not over powered these classes include scout  the nimble fastrunning caffinated  that can dominate the game if the player is a good scout player or can be taken out very easily soldier  one of the few classes that newbie players tend to pick first soldier uses a rocket launcher to take down his foes and gib them soldier has 200 hp and can be taken out with a few hits from the scouts scattergun but if played right the soldier can also dominate the team pyro this unknownthing uses a flamethrower to burn his enimies to a crisp and can be taken out but normally its taken out from a long distance pyro is great for close combat same with the scout and while heshes not a class for newbie players heshe can take out enimies within seconds demoman  a bombweilding drunk that uses projectiles bombsstickies to trap foes andor stratigically place them to gib enemies demoman is not recommended for newbie players at all but mostly because his tactics are very hard to get a good grasp of and he can take a long time to get used to and master heavy  the posterboy of tf2 the giant russian man with a minigun this big dude is can be one of the biggest threats in tf2 as far as classes go and can take down any of the 9 classes with ease by no means is the heavy overpowered but he can definately get quite a few kills in heavy is also another newbie favourite and hes recommended for newbie players because of his very easy tactics and gameplay style engineer  the texan wearing the hardhat engineer also referred as engie or engy ehngee uses sentry guns dispencers and teleporters to fight in the battle engineer is also equipped with a shotgun pistol and a wrench engineer definately takes time to learn master and use mostly because the player needs patience building sentry guns take awhile to level up from 1 to level 3 and the player also needs to know when and how to use hisher sentry gun engie definately isnt a newbiefriendly class and will take some time to learn medic  the german medic that heals his dear comerades in the fight for victory medic is selfexplanitory he heals teammates in battle but has different tactics of playing the tf2 community has come up with a name for one of thembattle medic and this is used when a player uses medic to fight using his needle gun or his crossbow that is unlockablecraftablebuyable at any given time rather than using his medigun to heal his teammates medic is an overall respected class and although he may seem a little complicated he is a little newbiefriendly mostly because his point in the game is very easy to understand and he is overall an easy class to use sniper  the australian sniper that isnt mlg o the sniper also referred after his name mundy is nothing like any other sniper youve ever played as if youre a cod player transferring over into tf2 youll be starting a new leaf because his gameplay is absolutely nothing like cod or any modern shooter first of all there is no such thing as quickscoping or 360 headshot noscope unless you consider a hip fire to be a noscope the snipers gun doesnt give out an amazing amount of damage right as you scoper in you need to wait a little while there is a charge meter until the sniper will do its fullest amount of damage snipers aim for the heads of their enemies and even if its not a fully charged shot the headshot will normally do 75100 damage to any given foe sniper is almost always picked by newbie players especially cod people transferring to tf2 mostly because his tactics and gameplay is amazingly easy and insanely simple to understand last class spy  le spy the french guy who stole your mother  your mother and is right behind you the spy is adored by almost everyone being notorious for his backstab if you backstab someone using your knife its an instant kill dealing over 1300 damage to any given foe the spy can be a very sneaky class to choose and he can mean the life or the death of your team if you know how to use the spy youre more than likely to save your entire team hes that powerful on the other hand if youre a newbie and you have no idea how to use the spy your team will most likely fail because of a couple of reasons spies are generally targeted by most classes such as heavy sniper and pyro which means that if youre caught by the enemy team or you are revealed to the enemy team you will be put on high alert and you will most likely find spy checkers spy checkers are normally pyros who try to set their team mates on fire if youre a pyro on the blue team and you use your flame thrower on a real team mate the fire will not affect them and they will be fine but if they use their flame thrower on a red spy that is diguised as their team mate they will burst in flames and you will be revealed checking their teammates spy is also a very hard class to master which is why hes not recommended to newbie players thats the general description of all the 9 classes you can choose from in tf2 overall tf2 is a great balanced fun and absolutely amazing multiplayer first person shooter that will never fail to impress you will always find someone playing the game no doubt about it and there are countless servers that are ran daily ranging from pub serversvalve servers to custom made map servers there are many ways to enjoy tf2 and you will certanly never feel bored because there is almost always something new to enjoy in tf2 tf2 has been an amazing game that has developed into something completely bigger than valve had probably imagined thanks for reading my 10 hour long essay and novel written by sonic the hedgehog  twd kenny 1010
