tldr at the end it was 2011 i had been wandering around best buy when i saw a box case for team fortress 2 for 10 dollars i wondered why they would be selling the same minimalist game i played on the orange box on my xbox so i wandered over to the computer section of the store and looked up why someone would buy it on pc i found that the pc version had more than the 10 maps on the xbox version it had differnt weapons to pick from and hats too i thought oh what the hell and got the game i came home to set it up on my old cruddy toshiba laptop and as a result caused me to create a steam account but it couldnt hande it so i used my brothers laptop whenever he wasnt using it i fell in love instantly the multitudes of gamemodes the custom maps and many achievements to get and i was an achievement addict back then thanks to my xbox kept me entertained my brother got a virus on his computer and blames the custom maps i downloaded because of it to this day im not sure if it was the cause so he didnt let me use it anymore almost a year later it was early 2012 somehow i convinced my brother to play on his computer again when i found out that a few months earlier the game became free to play a ton of my friends began playing it which made it appealing again when i came back though everything was about trading not many went to achievement servers anymore there were spreadsheets and things that used to be worth very little buds were 2 keys and bills were 1 were now jacked up in price i got used to it though and adapted to become a good trader i even met a guy who i called my partner and we worked together to trade our way up and it worked we got a fireproof diary which i still dont know what it does out of pyromania despite me finding the deal he wanted to hold on to it and around that time i felt him becoming more hostile i was kind of afraid to ask him to much out of fear that he would run off with the whole thing and despite my pleads in saying that it would probably triple in value soon it only doubled but i was still kind of right he decided to sell it anyway and because of my conversations with him being too cautious he only gave me 25%  5 keys out of 20 and i couldnt really do much about it i was angry so i created a scheme in which i created a fake account and pretended i had some crazy amount to offer him in a spycrab look it up if you dont know what it is and knowing him he said he had an equal amount which he didnt i got lucky and i won it and just like i thought he changed his name and did a bunch of other things to hide himself i then used a new fake account which i pretended was a steam admin of something like that and told him when he was reported for the spycrab i investigated and found that the bud he used to have was duped look that up too he practically bribed me to keep quiet and i got back a good share of what was mine he still doesnt know i did this to this day i lost my tf2 privalages again until late 2013 this year when i got my own computer and this was the best time of all for me from all my previous trading i had a ton of items which raised in value while i was away i decided as i didnt need most of it to do giveaways in different servers one server in particular sodahappy i met a kind admin still good friends with who helped me do some giveaways using his admin powers this influenced me to join the community and become a moderator so i could do giveways for a while it was fun people didnt do the giveaways for only free stuff but for the fun minigames it had such as one where everyone was locked in a small room and had to try and run away while i used a zap function which killed them if i pressed a button while aiming at them but then problems started to occur my giveaways started to become out of hand as everyone was doing them people no longer cared for the game than the prize and i got in trouble with the higher up admins because of the amount of zaps  i had 2800 zaps in the 4 months i was a mod other mods had no more than 100 in their entire careers after explaing that issue and a few others i was restricted in giveaways and over time i got less enthusiastic with it i left sodahappy but i left with a ton of new and good friends on my side who i met through the server in the recent months i focused on getting my dream unusual which i wanted long since before free to play was a thing a texas ten gallon painted gold that was vivid plasma and level 3 or 33 favorite hat favorite paint favorite effect and if you look at my name you can see why the level after borrowing an entire bud from that admin mentioned above from sodahappy the first one i met i purchased the hat for 35 buds with some extra sweets while it was only worth 25 this was because the owner was super reluctant to give it up but i needed it for its level 33 after paying off the 1 bud debt i felt complete i had a ton of tf2 stuff including my dream hat and i felt it was time to move on so i gave a lot of my stuff away and stopped playing tf2 revisiting occasionally summarytldr tf2 is my most played game of all time and i kind of grew up with it and if i could go back and change anything i wouldnt maybe except for that  scamming me as much as it makes me sound like a nerd tf2 represents a chapter of my life and i wont soon forget it
